member.name: T:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore
member.summary: This class contains information about a species observation in Darwin Core 1.5 compatible format. Further information about the properties can be found at http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.AccessRights
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: dcterms:accessRights. Information about who can access the resource or an indication of its security status. Access Rights may include information regarding access or restrictions based on privacy, security, or other policies.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.BasisOfRecord
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: basisOfRecord. The specific nature of the data record - a subtype of the dcterms:type. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Darwin Core Type Vocabulary (http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/type-vocabulary/index.htm). In Species Gateway this property has the value HumanObservation.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.BibliographicCitation
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: dcterms:bibliographicCitation. A bibliographic reference for the resource as a statement indicating how this record should be cited (attributed) when used. Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.CollectionCode
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: collectionCode. The name, acronym, coden, or initialism identifying the collection or data set from which the record was derived.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.CollectionID
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: collectionID. An identifier for the collection or dataset from which the record was derived. For physical specimens, the recommended best practice is to use the identifier in a collections registry such as the Biodiversity Collections Index (http://www.biodiversitycollectionsindex.org/).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.DataGeneralizations
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: dataGeneralizations. Actions taken to make the shared data less specific or complete than in its original form. Suggests that alternative data of higher quality may be available on request.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.DatasetID
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: datasetID. An identifier for the set of data. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to a collection or institution.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.DatasetName
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: datasetName. The name identifying the data set from which the record was derived.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.DynamicProperties
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: dynamicProperties. A list (concatenated and separated) of additional measurements, facts, characteristics, or assertions about the record. Meant to provide a mechanism for structured content such as key-value pairs.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.Event
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: Event. The category of information pertaining to an event (an action that occurs at a place and during a period of time).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.GeologicalContext
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: GeologicalContext. The category of information pertaining to a location within a geological context, such as stratigraphy.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.Identification
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: Identification. The category of information pertaining to taxonomic determinations (the assignment of a scientific name).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.InformationWithheld
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: informationWithheld. Additional information that exists, but that has not been shared in the given record.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.InstitutionCode
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: institutionCode. The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record. Currently this property has the value ArtDatabanken.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.InstitutionID
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: institutionID. An identifier for the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.IsInEconomicZoneOfSweden
member.summary: Internal flag used in validation. must be true to be stored in processed data

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.Language
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: dcterms:language. A language of the resource. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as RFC 4646 [RFC4646].

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.License
member.summary: A legal document giving official permission to do something with the resource.
member.example: http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/legalcode, http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.Location
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: dcterms:Location. A spatial region or named place. For Darwin Core, a set of terms describing a place, whether named or not.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.MaterialSample
member.summary: A physical result of a sampling (or subsampling) event. In biological collections, the material sample is typically collected, and either preserved or destructively processed.
member.example: A whole organism preserved in a collection. A part of an organism isolated for some purpose. A soil sample. A marine microbial sample.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.MeasurementOrFact
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: MeasurementOrFact. The category of information pertaining to measurements, facts, characteristics, or assertions about a resource (instance of data record, such as Occurrence, Taxon, Location, Event).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.Modified
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: dcterms:modified. The most recent date-time on which the resource was changed. For Darwin Core, recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.Occurrence
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: Occurrence. The category of information pertaining to evidence of an occurrence in nature, in a collection, or in a dataset (specimen, observation, etc.).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.Organism
member.summary: Instances of the dwc:Organism class are intended to facilitate linking one or more dwc:Identification instances to one or more dwc:Occurrence instances.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.OwnerInstitutionCode
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: ownerInstitutionCode. The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having ownership of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.References
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: dcterms:references. A related resource that is referenced, cited, or otherwise pointed to by the described resource.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.ResourceRelationship
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: ResourceRelationship. The category of information pertaining to relationships between resources (instances of data records, such as Occurrences, Taxa, Locations, Events).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.Rights
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: dcterms:rights. Information about rights held in and over the resource. Typically, rights information includes a statement about various property rights associated with the resource, including intellectual property rights.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.RightsHolder
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: dcterms:rightsHolder. A person or organization owning or managing rights over the resource.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.Taxon
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: Taxon. The category of information pertaining to taxonomic names, taxon name usages, or taxon concepts.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCore.Type
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: dcterms:type. The nature or genre of the resource. For Darwin Core, recommended best practice is to use the name of the class that defines the root of the record.

member.name: T:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreConservation
member.summary: Not defined in Darwin Core. Conservation related information about the taxon that the species observation is attached to.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreConservation.ActionPlan
member.summary: Not defined in Darwin Core. This property indicates whether the species is the subject of an action plan ('åtgärdsprogram' in swedish).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreConservation.ConservationRelevant
member.summary: Not defined in Darwin Core. This property indicates whether a species has been classified as nature conservation relevant ('naturvårdsintressant' in swedish). The concept 'nature conservation relevant' must be defined before this property can be used.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreConservation.Natura2000
member.summary: Not defined in Darwin Core. This property indicates whether the species is included in Natura 2000.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreConservation.ProtectedByLaw
member.summary: Not defined in Darwin Core. This property indicates whether the species is protected by the law in Sweden.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreConservation.ProtectionLevel
member.summary: Not defined in Darwin Core. Information about how protected information about a species is in Sweden. Currently this is a value between 1 to 5. 1 indicates public access and 5 is the highest used security level.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreConservation.RedlistCategory
member.summary: Not defined in Darwin Core. Redlist category for redlisted species. The property also contains information about which redlist that is referenced. Example value: CR (Sweden, 2010). Possible redlist values are DD (Data Deficient), EX (Extinct), RE (Regionally Extinct), CR (Critically Endangered), EN (Endangered), VU (Vulnerable), NT (Near Threatened). Not redlisted species has no value in this property.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreConservation.SwedishImmigrationHistory
member.summary: Not defined in Darwin Core. This property contains information about the species immigration history.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreConservation.SwedishOccurrence
member.summary: Not defined in Darwin Core. Information about the species occurrence in Sweden. For example information about if the species reproduce in sweden.

member.name: T:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent
member.summary: This class contains event information about a species observation in Darwin Core 1.5 compatible format. Further information about the properties can be found at http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.Day
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: day. The integer day of the month on which the Event occurred (start date of observation).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.EndDayOfYear
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: endDayOfYear. The latest ordinal day of the year on which the Event occurred (1 for January 1, 365 for December 31, except in a leap year, in which case it is 366).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.EventDate
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: eventDate. The date-time or interval during which an Event occurred. For occurrences, this is the date-time when the event was recorded. Not suitable for a time in a geological context. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E). For example: ”2007-03-01 13:00:00 - 2008-05-11 15:30:00”

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.EventID
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: eventID. A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, global unique identifier, URI) of media associated with the Occurrence.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.EventRemarks
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: eventRemarks. Comments or notes about the Event.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.EventTime
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: eventTime. The time or interval during which an Event occurred. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E). For example: ”13:00:00 - 15:30:00”

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.FieldNotes
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: fieldNotes. One of a) an indicator of the existence of, b) a reference to (publication, URI), or c) the text of notes taken in the field about the Event.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.FieldNumber
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: fieldNumber. An identifier given to the event in the field. Often serves as a link between field notes and the Event.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.Habitat
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: habitat. A category or description of the habitat in which the Event occurred.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.Month
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: month. The ordinal month in which the Event occurred.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.ParentEventID
member.summary: An identifier for the set of information associated with an Event (something that occurs at a place and time). May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.
member.example: A1 (parentEventID to identify the main Whittaker Plot in nested samples, each with its own eventID - A1:1, A1:2).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.SamplingEffort
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: samplingEffort. The amount of effort expended during an Event.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.SamplingProtocol
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: samplingProtocol. The name of, reference to, or description of the method or protocol used during an Event.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.SampleSizeUnit
member.summary: The unit of measurement of the size (time duration, length, area, or volume) of a sample in a sampling event. A sampleSizeUnit must have a corresponding sampleSizeValue, e.g., 5 for sampleSizeValue with metre for sampleSizeUnit.
member.example: minute, hour, day, metre, square metre, cubic metre

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.SampleSizeValue
member.summary: A numeric value for a measurement of the size (time duration, length, area, or volume) of a sample in a sampling event.
member.example: 5 for sampleSizeValue with metre for sampleSizeUnit.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.StartDayOfYear
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: startDayOfYear. The earliest ordinal day of the year on which the Event occurred (1 for January 1, 365 for December 31, except in a leap year, in which case it is 366).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.VerbatimEventDate
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: verbatimEventDate. The verbatim original representation of the date and time information for an Event.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreEvent.Year
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: year. The four-digit year in which the Event occurred, according to the Common Era Calendar.

member.name: T:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreIdentification

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreIdentification.DateIdentified
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: dateIdentified. The date on which the subject was identified as representing the Taxon. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreIdentification.IdentificationID
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: identificationID. An identifier for the Identification (the body of information associated with the assignment of a scientific name). May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreIdentification.IdentificationQualifier
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: identificationQualifier. A brief phrase or a standard term ("cf.", "aff.") to express the determiner's doubts about the Identification.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreIdentification.IdentificationReferences
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: identificationReferences. A list (concatenated and separated) of references (publication, global unique identifier, URI) used in the Identification.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreIdentification.IdentificationRemarks
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: identificationRemarks. Comments or notes about the Identification. Contains for example information about that the observer is uncertain about which species that has been observed.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreIdentification.IdentificationVerificationStatus
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: identificationVerificationStatus. A categorical indicator of the extent to which the taxonomic identification has been verified to be correct. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as that used in HISPID/ABCD.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreIdentification.IdentifiedBy
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: identifiedBy. A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who assigned the Taxon to the subject.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreIdentification.TypeStatus
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: typeStatus. A list (concatenated and separated) of nomenclatural types (type status, typified scientific name, publication) applied to the subject.

member.name: T:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation
member.summary: This class contains location information about a species observation in Darwin Core 1.5 compatible format. Further information about the properties can be found at http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.Continent
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: continent. The name of the continent in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographi Names or the ISO 3166 Continent code.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.CoordinatePrecision
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: CoordinatePrecision. A decimal representation of the precision of the coordinates given in the DecimalLatitude and DecimalLongitude.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.CoordinateUncertaintyInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: coordinateUncertaintyInMeters. The horizontal distance (in meters) from the given CoordinateX and CoordinateY describing the smallest circle containing the whole of the Location. Leave the value empty if the uncertainty is unknown, cannot be estimated, or is not applicable (because there are no coordinates). Zero is not a valid value for this term.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.Country
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: country. The name of the country or major administrative unit in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.CountryCode
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: countryCode. The standard code for the country in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use ISO 3166-1-alpha-2 country codes.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.County
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: county. The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region than stateProvince(county, shire, department, etc.) in which the Location occurs ('län' in swedish).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.DecimalLatitude
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: decimalLatitude. Definition in Darwin Core: The geographic latitude (in decimal degrees, using the spatial reference system given in geodeticDatum) of the geographic center of a Location. Positive values are north of the Equator, negative values are south of it. Legal values lie between -90 and 90, inclusive.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.DecimalLongitude
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: decimalLongitude. Definition in Darwin Core: The geographic longitude (in decimal degrees, using the spatial reference system given in geodeticDatum) of the geographic center of a Location. Positive values are east of the Greenwich Meridian, negative values are west of it. Legal values lie between -180 and 180, inclusive.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.FootprintSpatialFit
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: footprintSpatialFit. The ratio of the area of the footprint (footprintWKT) to the area of the true (original, or most specific) spatial representation of the Location. Legal values are 0, greater than or equal to 1, or undefined. A value of 1 is an exact match or 100% overlap. A value of 0 should be used if the given footprint does not completely contain the original representation. The footprintSpatialFit is undefined (and should be left blank) if the original representation is a point and the given georeference is not that same point. If both the original and the given georeference are the same point, the footprintSpatialFit is 1.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.FootprintSRS
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: footprintSRS. A Well-Known Text (WKT) representation of the Spatial Reference System (SRS) for the footprintWKT of the Location. Do not use this term to describe the SRS of the decimalLatitude and decimalLongitude, even if it is the same as for the footprintWKT - use the geodeticDatum instead.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.FootprintWKT
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: footprintWKT. A Well-Known Text (WKT) representation of the shape (footprint, geometry) that defines the Location. A Location may have both a point-radius representation (see decimalLatitude) and a footprint representation, and they may differ from each other.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.GeodeticDatum
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: geodeticDatum. The ellipsoid, geodetic datum, or spatial reference system (SRS) upon which the geographic coordinates given in decimalLatitude and decimalLongitude as based. Recommended best practice is use the EPSG code as a controlled vocabulary to provide an SRS, if known. Otherwise use a controlled vocabulary for the name or code of the geodetic datum, if known. Otherwise use a controlled vocabulary for the name or code of the ellipsoid, if known. If none of these is known, use the value "unknown".

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.GeoreferencedBy
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: georeferencedBy. A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who determined the georeference (spatial representation) the Location.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.GeoreferencedDate
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: georeferencedDate. The date on which the Location was georeferenced. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.GeoreferenceProtocol
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: georeferenceProtocol. A description or reference to the methods used to determine the spatial footprint, coordinates, and uncertainties.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.GeoreferenceRemarks
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: georeferenceRemarks. Notes or comments about the spatial description determination, explaining assumptions made in addition or opposition to the those formalized in the method referred to in georeferenceProtocol.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.GeoreferenceSources
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: georeferenceSources. A list (concatenated and separated) of maps, gazetteers, or other resources used to georeference the Location, described specifically enough to allow anyone in the future to use the same resources.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.GeoreferenceVerificationStatus
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: georeferenceVerificationStatus. A categorical description of the extent to which the georeference has been verified to represent the best possible spatial description. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.HigherGeography
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: higherGeography. A list (concatenated and separated) of geographic names less specific than the information captured in the locality term.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.HigherGeographyID
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: higherGeographyID. An identifier for the geographic region within which the Location occurred. Recommended best practice is to use an persistent identifier from a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.Island
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: island. The name of the island on or near which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.IslandGroup
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: islandGroup. The name of the island group in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.Locality
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: locality. The specific description of the place. Less specific geographic information can be provided in other geographic terms (higherGeography, continent, country, stateProvince, county, municipality, waterBody, island, islandGroup). This term may contain information modified from the original to correct perceived errors or standardize the description.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.LocationAccordingTo
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: locationAccordingTo. Information about the source of this Location information. Could be a publication (gazetteer), institution, or team of individuals.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.LocationID
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: locationID. An identifier for the set of location information (data associated with dcterms:Location). May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.LocationRemarks
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: locationRemarks. Comments or notes about the Location.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.MaximumDepthInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: maximumDepthInMeters. The greater depth of a range of depth below the local surface, in meters.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.MaximumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: maximumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters. The greater distance in a range of distance from a reference surface in the vertical direction, in meters. Use positive values for locations above the surface, negative values for locations below. If depth measures are given, the reference surface is the location given by the depth, otherwise the reference surface is the location given by the elevation.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.MaximumElevationInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: maximumElevationInMeters. The upper limit of the range of elevation (altitude, usually above sea level), in meters.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.MinimumDepthInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: minimumDepthInMeters. The lesser depth of a range of depth below the local surface, in meters.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.MinimumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: minimumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters. The lesser distance in a range of distance from a reference surface in the vertical direction, in meters. Use positive values for locations above the surface, negative values for locations below. If depth measures are given, the reference surface is the location given by the depth, otherwise the reference surface is the location given by the elevation.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.MinimumElevationInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: minimumElevationInMeters. The lower limit of the range of elevation (altitude, usually above sea level), in meters.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.Municipality
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: municipality. The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region than county (city, municipality, etc.) in which the Location occurs. Do not use this term for a nearby named place that does not contain the actual location.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.PointRadiusSpatialFit
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: pointRadiusSpatialFit. The ratio of the area of the point-radius (decimalLatitude, decimalLongitude, coordinateUncertaintyInMeters) to the area of the true (original, or most specific) spatial representation of the Location. Legal values are 0, greater than or equal to 1, or undefined. A value of 1 is an exact match or 100% overlap. A value of 0 should be used if the given point-radius does not completely contain the original representation. The pointRadiusSpatialFit is undefined (and should be left blank) if the original representation is a point without uncertainty and the given georeference is not that same point (without uncertainty). If both the original and the given georeference are the same point, the pointRadiusSpatialFit is 1.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.StateProvince
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: stateProvince. The name of the next smaller administrative region than country (state, province, canton, department, region, etc.) in which the Location occurs. ('landskap' in swedish).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.VerbatimCoordinates
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: verbatimCoordinates. The verbatim original spatial coordinates of the Location. The coordinate ellipsoid, geodeticDatum, or full Spatial Reference System (SRS) for these coordinates should be stored in verbatimSRS and the coordinate system should be stored in verbatimCoordinateSystem.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.VerbatimCoordinateSystem
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: verbatimCoordinateSystem. The spatial coordinate system for the verbatimLatitude and verbatimLongitude or the verbatimCoordinates of the Location. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.VerbatimDepth
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: verbatimDepth. The original description of the depth below the local surface.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.VerbatimElevation
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: verbatimElevation. The original description of the elevation (altitude, usually above sea level) of the Location.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.VerbatimLatitude
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: verbatimLatitude. The verbatim original latitude of the Location. The coordinate ellipsoid, geodeticDatum, or full Spatial Reference System (SRS) for these coordinates should be stored in verbatimSRS and the coordinate system should be stored in verbatimCoordinateSystem.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.VerbatimLocality
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: verbatimLocality. The original textual description of the place.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.VerbatimLongitude
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: verbatimLongitude. The verbatim original longitude of the Location. The coordinate ellipsoid, geodeticDatum, or full Spatial Reference System (SRS) for these coordinates should be stored in verbatimSRS and the coordinate system should be stored in verbatimCoordinateSystem.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.VerbatimSRS
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: verbatimSRS. The ellipsoid, geodetic datum, or spatial reference system (SRS) upon which coordinates given in verbatimLatitude and verbatimLongitude, or verbatimCoordinates are based. Recommended best practice is use the EPSG code as a controlled vocabulary to provide an SRS, if known. Otherwise use a controlled vocabulary for the name or code of the geodetic datum, if known. Otherwise use a controlled vocabulary for the name or code of the ellipsoid, if known. If none of these is known, use the value "unknown".

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreLocation.WaterBody
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: waterBody. The name of the water body in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

member.name: T:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreMaterialSample
member.summary: A physical result of a sampling (or subsampling) event. In biological collections, the material sample is typically collected, and either preserved or destructively processed.
member.example: A whole organism preserved in a collection. A part of an organism isolated for some purpose. A soil sample. A marine microbial sample.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreMaterialSample.MaterialSampleID
member.summary: An identifier for the MaterialSample (as opposed to a particular digital record of the material sample). In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make the materialSampleID globally unique.

member.name: T:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreMeasurementOrFact
member.summary: A measurement of or fact about an rdfs:Resource (http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#Resource). Resources can be thought of as identifiable records or instances of classes and may include, but need not be limited to dwc:Occurrence, dwc:Organism, dwc:MaterialSample, dwc:Event, dwc:Location, dwc:GeologicalContext, dwc:Identification, or dwc:Taxon.
member.example: The weight of an organism in grams. The number of placental scars. Surface water temperature in Celsius.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreMeasurementOrFact.MeasurementAccuracy
member.summary: The description of the potential error associated with the measurementValue.
member.example: 0.01, normal distribution with variation of 2 m

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreMeasurementOrFact.MeasurementDeterminedBy
member.summary: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who determined the value of the MeasurementOrFact. Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space ( | ).
member.example: Rob Guralnick, Peter Desmet | Stijn Van Hoey

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreMeasurementOrFact.MeasurementDeterminedDate
member.summary: The date on which the MeasurementOrFact was made. Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601:2004(E).
member.example: 1963-03-08T14:07-0600 (8 Mar 1963 at 2:07pm in the time zone six hours earlier than UTC). 2009-02-20T08:40Z (20 February 2009 8:40am UTC). 2018-08-29T15:19 (3:19pm local time on 29 August 2018). 1809-02-12 (some time during 12 February 1809). 1906-06 (some time in June 1906). 1971 (some time in the year 1971). 2007-03-01T13:00:00Z/2008-05-11T15:30:00Z (some time during the interval between 1 March 2007 1pm UTC and 11 May 2008 3:30pm UTC). 1900/1909 (some time during the interval between the beginning of the year 1900 and the end of the year 1909). 2007-11-13/15 (some time in the interval between 13 November 2007 and 15 November 2007).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreMeasurementOrFact.MeasurementID
member.summary: An identifier for the MeasurementOrFact (information pertaining to measurements, facts, characteristics, or assertions). May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreMeasurementOrFact.MeasurementMethod
member.summary: A description of or reference to (publication, URI) the method or protocol used to determine the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.
member.example: minimum convex polygon around burrow entrances (for a home range area). barometric altimeter (for an elevation).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreMeasurementOrFact.MeasurementRemarks
member.summary: Comments or notes accompanying the MeasurementOrFact.
member.example: tip of tail missing

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreMeasurementOrFact.MeasurementType
member.summary: The nature of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.
member.example: tail length, temperature, trap line length, survey area, trap type

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreMeasurementOrFact.MeasurementUnit
member.summary: The units associated with the measurementValue Recommended best practice is to use the International System of Units (SI).
member.example: mm, C, km, ha

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreMeasurementOrFact.MeasurementValue
member.summary: The value of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.

member.name: T:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence
member.summary: This class contains occurrence information about a species observation in Darwin Core 1.5 compatible format. Further information about the properties can be found at http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.AssociatedMedia
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: associatedMedia. A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, global unique identifier, URI) of media associated with the Occurrence.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.AssociatedOccurrences
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: associatedOccurrences. A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers of other Occurrence records and their associations to this Occurrence.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.AssociatedReferences
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: associatedReferences. A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with the Occurrence.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.AssociatedSequences
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: associatedSequences. A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers of other Occurrence records and their associations to this Occurrence.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.AssociatedTaxa
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: associatedTaxa. A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers or names of taxa and their associations with the Occurrence.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.Behavior
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: behavior. A description of the behavior shown by the subject at the time the Occurrence was recorded. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.CatalogNumber
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: catalogNumber. An identifier (preferably unique) for the record within the data set or collection.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.Disposition
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: disposition. The current state of a specimen with respect to the collection identified in collectionCode or collectionID. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.EstablishmentMeans
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: establishmentMeans. The process by which the biological individual(s) represented in the Occurrence became established at the location. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.IndividualCount
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: individualCount. The number of individuals represented present at the time of the Occurrence.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.IndividualID
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: individualID. An identifier for an individual or named group of individual organisms represented in the Occurrence. Meant to accommodate resampling of the same individual or group for monitoring purposes. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to a data set.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.LifeStage
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: lifeStage. The age class or life stage of the biological individual(s) at the time the Occurrence was recorded. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.OccurrenceID
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: occurrenceID. An identifier for the Occurrence (as opposed to a particular digital record of the occurrence). In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make the occurrenceID globally unique. The format LSID (Life Science Identifiers) is used as GUID (Globally unique identifier) for species observations. Currently known GUIDs: Species Gateway (Artportalen) 1, urn:lsid:artportalen.se:Sighting:{reporting system}.{id} where {reporting system} is one of Bird, Bugs, Fish, MarineInvertebrates, PlantAndMushroom or Vertebrate. Species Gateway (Artportalen) 2, urn:lsid:artportalen.se:Sighting:{id} Red list database: urn:lsid:artdata.slu.se:SpeciesObservation:{id}

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.OccurrenceRemarks
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: occurrenceRemarks. Comments or notes about the Occurrence.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.OccurrenceStatus
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: occurrenceStatus. A statement about the presence or absence of a Taxon at a Location. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.OtherCatalogNumbers
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: otherCatalogNumbers. A list (concatenated and separated) of previous or alternate fully qualified catalog numbers or other human-used identifiers for the same Occurrence, whether in the current or any other data set or collection.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.OrganismQuantity
member.summary: A number or enumeration value for the quantity of organisms. A dwc:organismQuantity must have a corresponding dwc:organismQuantityType.
member.example: 27 (organismQuantity) with individuals (organismQuantityType). 12.5 (organismQuantity) with %biomass (organismQuantityType). r (organismQuantity) with BraunBlanquetScale (organismQuantityType).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.OrganismQuantityType
member.summary: The type of quantification system used for the quantity of organisms. A dwc:organismQuantityType must have a corresponding dwc:organismQuantity.
member.example: 27 (organismQuantity) with individuals (organismQuantityType). 12.5 (organismQuantity) with %biomass (organismQuantityType). r (organismQuantity) with BraunBlanquetScale (organismQuantityType).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.Preparations
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: preparations. A list (concatenated and separated) of preparations and preservation methods for a specimen.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.PreviousIdentifications
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: previousIdentifications. A list (concatenated and separated) of previous assignments of names to the Occurrence.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.RecordedBy
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: recordedBy. A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations responsible for recording the original Occurrence. The primary collector or observer, especially one who applies a personal identifier (recordNumber), should be listed first.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.RecordNumber
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: recordNumber. An identifier given to the Occurrence at the time it was recorded. Often serves as a link between field notes and an Occurrence record, such as a specimen collector's number.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.ReproductiveCondition
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: reproductiveCondition. The reproductive condition of the biological individual(s) represented in the Occurrence. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOccurrence.Sex
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: sex. The sex of the biological individual(s) represented in the Occurrence. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

member.name: T:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.DarwinCoreOrganism
member.summary: Definition: A particular organism or defined group of organisms considered to be taxonomically homogeneous. Comments: Instances of the dwc:Organism class are intended to facilitate linking one or more dwc:Identification instances to one or more dwc:Occurrence instances. Therefore, things that are typically assigned scientific names (such as viruses, hybrids, and lichens) and aggregates whose occurrences are typically recorded (such as packs, clones, and colonies) are included in the scope of this class. Examples: A specific bird. A specific wolf pack. A specific instance of a bacterial culture.

member.name: T:SOS.Lib.Models.DarwinCore.ExtendedMeasurementOrFactRow
member.summary: ExtendedMeasurementOrFact Row. Support for generic measurements or facts, extended version linking to occurrences. This extension (eMoF) was developed to be used in combination with the Event Core, but is also compatible with other cores. When used with Event Core it allows to create an additional link between the eMoF and the occurrence extension. The eMoF can store measurements or facts related to a biological occurrence, environmental measurements or facts and sampling method attributes. This extension also provides the option to provide identifiers to reference a vocabulary for the measurementType, measurementValue and measurementUnit fields.

This identifier can reference a controlled vocabulary (e.g. for sampling instrument names, methodologies, life stages) or reference a methodology paper with a DOI. When the measurementValue refers to a value and not to a fact, the measurementvalueID has no meaning and should remain empty.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedIdentification.IdentificationId

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedIdentification.IdentificationQualifier
member.summary: A brief phrase or a standard term ("cf.", "aff.") to express the determiner's doubts about the Identification.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedIdentification.IdentificationReferences
member.summary: A list (concatenated and separated) of references (publication, global unique identifier, URI) used in the Identification.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedIdentification.IdentificationRemarks
member.summary: Comments or notes about the Identification. Contains for example information about that the observer is uncertain about which species that has been observed.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedIdentification.ValidationStatus

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedIdentification.IdentifiedByInternal
member.summary: List of userids and aliases matching the IdentifiedBy string, internal use only

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedIdentification.TypeStatus

member.name: T:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation
member.summary: This class contains location information about a species sighting location

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.Continent
member.summary: The name of the continent in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographi Names or the ISO 3166 Continent code. ('län' in swedish).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.CoordinatePrecision
member.summary: A decimal representation of the precision of the coordinates given in the DecimalLatitude and DecimalLongitude.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.CoordinateUncertaintyInMeters
member.summary: The horizontal distance (in meters) from the given CoordinateX and CoordinateY describing the smallest circle containing the whole of the Location. Leave the value empty if the uncertainty is unknown, cannot be estimated, or is not applicable (because there are no coordinates). Zero is not a valid value for this term.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.Country
member.summary: The name of the country or major administrative unit in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.CountryCode
member.summary: The standard code for the country in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use ISO 3166-1-alpha-2 country codes.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.County
member.summary: The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region than stateProvince(county, shire, department, etc.) in which the Location occurs ('län' in swedish).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.Municipality
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: municipality. The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region than county (city, municipality, etc.) in which the Location occurs.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.VerbatimMunicipality
member.summary: The original municipality value from data provider.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.Province
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: stateProvince. The name of the next smaller administrative region than country (state, province, canton, department, region, etc.) in which the Location occurs. ('landskap' in swedish).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.VerbatimProvince
member.summary: The original StateProvince value from data provider.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.DecimalLatitude
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: decimalLatitude. Definition in Darwin Core: The geographic latitude (in decimal degrees, using the spatial reference system given in geodeticDatum) of the geographic center of a Location. Positive values are north of the Equator, negative values are south of it. Legal values lie between -90 and 90, inclusive.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.DecimalLongitude
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: decimalLongitude. Definition in Darwin Core: The geographic longitude (in decimal degrees, using the spatial reference system given in geodeticDatum) of the geographic center of a Location. Positive values are east of the Greenwich Meridian, negative values are west of it. Legal values lie between -180 and 180, inclusive.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.FootprintSpatialFit
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: footprintSpatialFit. The ratio of the area of the footprint (footprintWKT) to the area of the true (original, or most specific) spatial representation of the Location. Legal values are 0, greater than or equal to 1, or undefined. A value of 1 is an exact match or 100% overlap. A value of 0 should be used if the given footprint does not completely contain the original representation. The footprintSpatialFit is undefined (and should be left blank) if the original representation is a point and the given georeference is not that same point. If both the original and the given georeference are the same point, the footprintSpatialFit is 1.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.FootprintSRS
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: footprintSRS. A Well-Known Text (WKT) representation of the Spatial Reference System (SRS) for the footprintWKT of the Location. Do not use this term to describe the SRS of the decimalLatitude and decimalLongitude, even if it is the same as for the footprintWKT - use the geodeticDatum instead.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.FootprintWKT
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: footprintWKT. A Well-Known Text (WKT) representation of the shape (footprint, geometry) that defines the Location. A Location may have both a point-radius representation (see decimalLatitude) and a footprint representation, and they may differ from each other.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.GeodeticDatum
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: geodeticDatum. The ellipsoid, geodetic datum, or spatial reference system (SRS) upon which the geographic coordinates given in decimalLatitude and decimalLongitude as based. Recommended best practice is use the EPSG code as a controlled vocabulary to provide an SRS, if known. Otherwise use a controlled vocabulary for the name or code of the geodetic datum, if known. Otherwise use a controlled vocabulary for the name or code of the ellipsoid, if known. If none of these is known, use the value "unknown".

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.GeoreferencedBy
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: georeferencedBy. A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who determined the georeference (spatial representation) the Location.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.GeoreferencedDate
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: georeferencedDate. The date on which the Location was georeferenced. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.GeoreferenceProtocol
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: georeferenceProtocol. A description or reference to the methods used to determine the spatial footprint, coordinates, and uncertainties.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.GeoreferenceRemarks
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: georeferenceRemarks. Notes or comments about the spatial description determination, explaining assumptions made in addition or opposition to the those formalized in the method referred to in georeferenceProtocol.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.GeoreferenceSources
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: georeferenceSources. A list (concatenated and separated) of maps, gazetteers, or other resources used to georeference the Location, described specifically enough to allow anyone in the future to use the same resources.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.GeoreferenceVerificationStatus
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: georeferenceVerificationStatus. A categorical description of the extent to which the georeference has been verified to represent the best possible spatial description. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.HigherGeography
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: higherGeography. A list (concatenated and separated) of geographic names less specific than the information captured in the locality term.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.HigherGeographyID
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: higherGeographyID. An identifier for the geographic region within which the Location occurred. Recommended best practice is to use an persistent identifier from a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.Island
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: island. The name of the island on or near which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.IslandGroup
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: islandGroup. The name of the island group in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.Locality
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: locality. The specific description of the place. Less specific geographic information can be provided in other geographic terms (higherGeography, continent, country, stateProvince, county, municipality, waterBody, island, islandGroup). This term may contain information modified from the original to correct perceived errors or standardize the description.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.LocationAccordingTo
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: locationAccordingTo. Information about the source of this Location information. Could be a publication (gazetteer), institution, or team of individuals.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.LocationId
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: locationID. An identifier for the set of location information (data associated with dcterms:Location). May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.LocationRemarks
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: locationRemarks. Comments or notes about the Location.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.MaximumDepthInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: maximumDepthInMeters. The greater depth of a range of depth below the local surface, in meters.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.MaximumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: maximumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters. The greater distance in a range of distance from a reference surface in the vertical direction, in meters. Use positive values for locations above the surface, negative values for locations below. If depth measures are given, the reference surface is the location given by the depth, otherwise the reference surface is the location given by the elevation.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.MaximumElevationInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: maximumElevationInMeters. The upper limit of the range of elevation (altitude, usually above sea level), in meters.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.MinimumDepthInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: minimumDepthInMeters. The lesser depth of a range of depth below the local surface, in meters.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.MinimumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: minimumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters. The lesser distance in a range of distance from a reference surface in the vertical direction, in meters. Use positive values for locations above the surface, negative values for locations below. If depth measures are given, the reference surface is the location given by the depth, otherwise the reference surface is the location given by the elevation.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.MinimumElevationInMeters
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: minimumElevationInMeters. The lower limit of the range of elevation (altitude, usually above sea level), in meters.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.PointLocation
member.summary: Point used in distance from point search

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.PointRadiusSpatialFit
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: pointRadiusSpatialFit. The ratio of the area of the point-radius (decimalLatitude, decimalLongitude, coordinateUncertaintyInMeters) to the area of the true (original, or most specific) spatial representation of the Location. Legal values are 0, greater than or equal to 1, or undefined. A value of 1 is an exact match or 100% overlap. A value of 0 should be used if the given point-radius does not completely contain the original representation. The pointRadiusSpatialFit is undefined (and should be left blank) if the original representation is a point without uncertainty and the given georeference is not that same point (without uncertainty). If both the original and the given georeference are the same point, the pointRadiusSpatialFit is 1.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.VerbatimCoordinates
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: verbatimCoordinates. The verbatim original spatial coordinates of the Location. The coordinate ellipsoid, geodeticDatum, or full Spatial Reference System (SRS) for these coordinates should be stored in verbatimSRS and the coordinate system should be stored in verbatimCoordinateSystem.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.VerbatimElevation

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.VerbatimLocality

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedLocation.VerbatimSRS

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedOccurrence.OccurrenceId
member.summary: An identifier for the Occurrence (as opposed to a particular digital record of the occurrence). In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make the occurrenceID globally unique. The format LSID (Life Science Identifiers) is used as GUID (Globally unique identifier) for species observations. Currently known GUIDs: Species Gateway (Artportalen) 1, urn:lsid:artportalen.se:Sighting:{reporting system}.{id} where {reporting system} is one of Bird, Bugs, Fish, MarineInvertebrates, PlantAndMushroom or Vertebrate. Species Gateway (Artportalen) 2, urn:lsid:artportalen.se:Sighting:{id} Red list database: urn:lsid:artdata.slu.se:SpeciesObservation:{id}

member.name: T:SOS.Lib.Models.Processed.Observation.ProcessedOrganism
member.summary: A particular organism or defined group of organisms considered to be taxonomically homogeneous.
member.remarks: Instances of the dwc:Organism class are intended to facilitate linking one or more dwc:Identification instances to one or more dwc:Occurrence instances. Therefore, things that are typically assigned scientific names (such as viruses, hybrids, and lichens) and aggregates whose occurrences are typically recorded (such as packs, clones, and colonies) are included in the scope of this class.

See also the wikipedia IS0 8601 entry for further explanation and examples.

The ratio of the area of the footprint (footprintWKT) to the area of the true (original, or most specific) spatial representation of the Location. Legal values are 0, greater than or equal to 1, or undefined. A value of 1 is an exact match or 100% overlap. Positive values are north of the Equator, negative values are south of it. Legal values lie between -90 and 90, inclusive.

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Verbatim.DarwinCore.DwcObservationVerbatim.DecimalLongitude

member.name: P:SOS.Lib.Models.Verbatim.DarwinCore.DwcObservationVerbatim.FootprintSpatialFit
member.summary: Darwin Core term name: footprintSpatialFit. The ratio of the area of the footprint (footprintWKT) to the area of the true (original, or most specific) spatial representation of the Location. Legal values are 0, greater than or equal to 1, or undefined. A value of 1 is an exact match or 100% overlap. A value of 0 should be used if the given footprint does not completely contain the original representation. The footprintSpatialFit is undefined (and should be left blank) if the original representation is a point and the given georeference is not that same point. If both the original and the given georeference are the same point, the footprintSpatialFit is 1. This property is currently not used.
